\layout Section

Conclusions
\layout Standard

The Automated Trading Desk does very interesting work, and requires very
 extensive knowledge and experience with C++ and with the software development
 cycle.
 It by far offers the most interesting and challenging work of the three
 companies.
 I have worked for CCIT in the past before it became part of healthcare.com,
 and am thus very familiar with the people there and with the specifics
 of the job, namely, the internals of the computer systems which they operate.
\layout Standard

As far as benefits go, the Automated Trading Desk appears to have the greatest
 benefits, though this is a very rough guess.
 I have only received one salary offer, though ATD is expected to offer
 much more.
 I have no information on an expected salary from Not a Number.
\layout Standard

Not a Number does graphics, which is extremely interesting.
 In fall of 1999, I took my first graphics course, and have loved the field
 ever since.
 A chance to work in the graphics field would be immeasurable, and could
 be a stepping stone for getting into the movie industry.
\layout Standard

Healthcare.com has the least commitment, which would make attending graduate
 school much easier later in my life.
 However, the employees who work for ATD are extraordinarily bright, and
 are likely to teach me much more than I might learn in a graduate program.
 The same is expected of Not a Number, as they have presented their product
 at SIGGRAPH, the largest graphics conference in the world.
\layout Standard

I am not applying for a job with Not a Number, as I feel the company has
 not matured enough to be a good choice (though this is purely a subjective
 evaluation).
 As a result, I cannot select it has my top choice.
 ATD does more interesting work than Healthcare.com, and appears to have
 a team of programmers with whom I can learn to work; Healthcare.com also
 has interesting people who I already know and trust.
 However, the greater salary and benefits that ATD is expected to provide
 is very appealing.
 Thus, ATD is my top choice.
